so I think it's still working.

00:11:35.280 --> 00:11:39.050
Joey, let me ask you, speaking
of composition, so you've

00:11:39.050 --> 00:11:42.330
done some really cool work
outside of the band as well,

00:11:42.330 --> 00:11:46.790
composing commercials, composing
movie and TV soundtracks,

00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:47.810
things like that.

00:11:47.810 --> 00:11:49.850
How does that process,
does it differ

00:11:49.850 --> 00:11:52.410
from what Charles was
just mentioning, where

00:11:52.410 --> 00:11:53.660
it's got a certain feel to it?

00:11:53.660 --> 00:11:55.970
Or does that feel completely
different than the type

00:11:55.970 --> 00:11:59.680
of music that you're producing
and creating with the Pixies?

00:11:59.680 --> 00:12:09.710
JOEY: It get very lonely just
by myself working all the time.

00:12:09.710 --> 00:12:11.330
Yeah, of course it
feels different.

00:12:11.330 --> 00:12:13.940
It's everyone's project.

00:12:13.940 --> 00:12:15.596
It's their pet.

00:12:15.596 --> 00:12:17.910
It's the last piece
of the puzzle.

00:12:17.910 --> 00:12:26.152
So I'm their slave?

00:12:26.152 --> 00:12:27.300
[LAUGHS]

00:12:27.300 --> 00:12:28.470
No.

00:12:28.470 --> 00:12:29.850
It's a fun process.

00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:33.180
It's amazing.

00:12:33.180 --> 00:12:37.770
My son, I was doing
a horror movie

00:12:37.770 --> 00:12:39.780
and I had him push a button.

00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:43.740
Well, a key, like
an ominous sound.

00:12:43.740 --> 00:12:47.340
And I go, when he walks
through that door, push it.

00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:51.140
And when he exits, take it out.

00:12:51.140 --> 00:12:52.080
I gave him $5.

00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:53.445
[LAUGHTER]

00:12:54.810 --> 00:12:56.070
JASON: That's pretty cool.

00:12:56.070 --> 00:12:58.840
And Paz, you helped out
with some of this as well.

00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:02.500
If you guys haven't
seen, a quick plug.

00:13:02.500 --> 00:13:05.670
Joey and Paz did a really
cool, I think it was Acura,

00:13:05.670 --> 00:13:06.510
am I right?

00:13:06.510 --> 00:13:09.526
An Acura commercial
maybe a year or two ago.

00:13:09.526 --> 00:13:10.900
And I might be
wrong on that too.

00:13:10.900 --> 00:13:13.191
But if you guys haven't seen
it, look it up on YouTube.

00:13:13.191 --> 00:13:15.570
It's actually one of
the coolest commercials.

00:13:15.570 --> 00:13:17.778
So you were able to kind of
work out on that as well,

00:13:17.778 --> 00:13:20.480
so expanding outside of the band
as well, which is fantastic.

00:13:20.480 --> 00:13:21.300
It's very cool.

00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:23.147
What was that
process like for you?

00:13:23.147 --> 00:13:25.230
You're classically trained,
I know, as a musician.

00:13:25.230 --> 00:13:27.240
Was that kind of fun to be
able to flex that a little bit?

00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:28.531
PAZ: That was really fun, yeah.

00:13:28.531 --> 00:13:31.290
I played piano and the
violin and I got my sister

00:13:31.290 --> 00:13:35.040
to play the cello on there.

00:13:35.040 --> 00:13:36.680
Just trying different
arrangements

00:13:36.680 --> 00:13:39.760
of "Where's My Mind."

00:13:39.760 --> 00:13:40.811
Yeah, it was really fun.

00:13:40.811 --> 00:13:41.310
JASON: Yeah.

00:13:41.310 --> 00:13:43.351
Well, hopefully we can
pump up some YouTube views

00:13:43.351 --> 00:13:45.000
on that commercial.

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:45.600
It's on there.

00:13:45.600 --> 00:13:47.671
I watched it recently.

00:13:47.671 --> 00:13:49.170
Let me talk a little
bit, so I guess

00:13:49.170 --> 00:13:50.461
we're talking about technology.

00:13:50.461 --> 00:13:54.570
And we are at Google, which
is a technology company.

00:13:54.570 --> 00:13:56.250
So usually when we
have bands in here,

00:13:56.250 --> 00:14:00.540
we like to ask a question
around how you guys feel

00:14:00.540 --> 00:14:03.270
about the utilization
of technology

00:14:03.270 --> 00:14:06.030
with what you guys do, whether
it's connectivity with fans,

00:14:06.030 --> 00:14:09.960
whether it's selling tickets,
whether it's social media

00:14:09.960 --> 00:14:13.080
and staying in touch
with family members.

00:14:13.080 --> 00:14:14.700
And you guys too,
I think you guys

00:14:14.700 --> 00:14:19.410
were I guess early quote,
unquote, "pioneers"

00:14:19.410 --> 00:14:22.170
in terms of your interaction
with digital media.

00:14:22.170 --> 00:14:25.260
You guys released a lot of
music on it was called eMusic.

00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:27.750
You guys were very
early to iTunes.

00:14:27.750 --> 00:14:29.310
So I feel like,
like it or not, you

00:14:29.310 --> 00:14:32.340
guys also embrace some of
the digital movement of music

00:14:32.340 --> 00:14:32.840
as well.

00:14:32.840 --> 00:14:35.700
So that's all encompassing
technology in general.

00:14:35.700 --> 00:14:37.380
But would just kind
of love to hear

00:14:37.380 --> 00:14:40.570
how you guys feel about
technology and music,

00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:42.390
whether it's been
good or bad and how

00:14:42.390 --> 00:14:45.330
that's worked for you guys.

00:14:45.330 --> 00:14:47.040
CHARLES: We had a
meeting this morning

00:14:47.040 --> 00:14:48.998
on the bus on the way
over here about the songs

00:14:48.998 --> 00:14:50.010
we were going to play.

00:14:50.010 --> 00:14:55.230
But also we discussed, I
guess we're a little behind.

00:14:55.230 --> 00:14:57.450
We told Simon, our
tour manager, that we

00:14:57.450 --> 00:15:00.480
wanted one of those
speakers that you just

00:15:00.480 --> 00:15:02.923
shout out and tell it
what music to play.

00:15:02.923 --> 00:15:05.550
There's Alexa, right?

00:15:05.550 --> 00:15:06.900
That's the one my brother has.

00:15:06.900 --> 00:15:08.557
JASON: I've never
heard of that one.

00:15:08.557 --> 00:15:09.930
[LAUGHTER]

00:15:09.930 --> 00:15:13.560
There's one called
Google Home, though.

00:15:13.560 --> 00:15:15.311
I've heard it's quite fantastic.

00:15:15.311 --> 00:15:16.560
CHARLES: Maybe get a free one.

00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:17.060
Maybe.

00:15:17.060 --> 00:15:18.530
I don't know.

00:15:18.530 --> 00:15:19.230
Google Home.

00:15:19.230 --> 00:15:21.510
We don't care, as long as
it plays the damn Chet Baker

00:15:21.510 --> 00:15:23.176
record or whatever
we want to listen to.

00:15:23.176 --> 00:15:25.530
You know what I mean?

00:15:25.530 --> 00:15:28.350
So yeah, we like the tech.

00:15:28.350 --> 00:15:30.870
JASON: Any other thoughts
from anyone else?

00:15:30.870 --> 00:15:32.960
JOEY: Technology is good.

00:15:32.960 --> 00:15:34.890
DAVID: One difference
from then and now

00:15:34.890 --> 00:15:38.609
is now there's Jumbo-trons
when you do live shows.

