00:20:44.617 --> 00:20:46.700
AUDIENCE: I guess I'd
direct this towards Charles,

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:49.580
going back in the
beginning days.

00:20:49.580 --> 00:20:51.520
What was the transition,
in other words,

00:20:51.520 --> 00:20:55.260
from playing music,
doing covers, and making

00:20:55.260 --> 00:20:57.960
that transition going
to original music?

00:20:57.960 --> 00:21:01.320
Could you tell us a little
bit about how that happened

00:21:01.320 --> 00:21:03.356
versus slugging it
out in the nightclubs?

00:21:03.356 --> 00:21:04.980
CHARLES: Well, we
played in nightclubs,

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:08.190
but we were playing in, I
don't know what you call it,

00:21:08.190 --> 00:21:12.210
a musical culture where you
didn't really do cover songs.

00:21:12.210 --> 00:21:14.970
If you do cover songs, you play
at a certain kind of a club.

00:21:14.970 --> 00:21:17.004
But the kind of clubs
that we were playing at,

00:21:17.004 --> 00:21:18.420
that would have
been frowned upon.

00:21:18.420 --> 00:21:20.459
You wouldn't have been
even allowed a slot.

00:21:20.459 --> 00:21:22.500
It doesn't matter what
kind of a racket you make,

00:21:22.500 --> 00:21:24.240
it has to be your
racket or whatever.

00:21:24.240 --> 00:21:29.640
So we've learned over the
years a couple of songs,

00:21:29.640 --> 00:21:31.590
but I personally find
it very challenging

00:21:31.590 --> 00:21:35.430
to learn other people's music,
even if it's a simple song,

00:21:35.430 --> 00:21:37.890
because it's confusing to me.

00:21:37.890 --> 00:21:38.880
I don't know.

00:21:38.880 --> 00:21:40.920
So we don't do a lot of covers.

00:21:40.920 --> 00:21:43.950
We never did when we
were starting out.

00:21:43.950 --> 00:21:46.290
But that's just
because we were playing

00:21:46.290 --> 00:21:50.880
in Boston and those
clubs there, it

00:21:50.880 --> 00:21:52.290
wasn't about
playing cover music.

00:21:52.290 --> 00:21:54.180
So I'm glad I didn't have to.

00:21:54.180 --> 00:21:56.190
Some people, they
might live in the town

00:21:56.190 --> 00:21:58.350
where that might be
the transition that you

00:21:58.350 --> 00:22:00.810
have to kind of go
through to, I don't know,

00:22:00.810 --> 00:22:03.300
get to that next stop.

00:22:03.300 --> 00:22:05.340
But we didn't have to do that.

00:22:08.450 --> 00:22:11.630
I don't know what we
would have played.

00:22:11.630 --> 00:22:12.860
Trying to think.

00:22:12.860 --> 00:22:14.210
I don't know.

00:22:14.210 --> 00:22:14.835
Probably like--

00:22:14.835 --> 00:22:15.584
JASON: Steely Dan?

00:22:15.584 --> 00:22:17.360
CHARLES: The Cars,
probably, or something.

